data.description:
1. The U.S. Chamber of Commerce is considering suing the Trump administration to stop global tariffs;
2. Justin Sun: TRON has more than 298 million users worldwide and is expected to exceed 300 million users within 10 days;
3. The Ethereum Foundation once again transferred 1,000 ETH to a multi-signature address, equivalent to about $1.58 million;
4. Cboe plans to launch new Bitcoin futures in cooperation with FTSE Russell, which will start trading on April 28 if approved;
5. CZ lowered its ReachMe private message pricing to 0.8 BNB;
6. The three major U.S. stock index futures rose, with the S&P 500 index futures rising 1.8%;
7. Matrixport: The RMB exchange rate is approaching key resistance levels, and Bitcoin may usher in a new round of increases;
8. Binance will launch FORTHUSDT perpetual contracts;
9. Institutions: Trump's tariffs may increase the core PCE index by 2.0%;
10. Binance announced the results of the first round of voting to delist tokens, and will delist 14 tokens including BADGER, BAL, BETA, etc.;
11. Bitget CEO: Bitcoin is still a relatively good choice after the tariff risk ends, and BTC has been added;
12. USDC Treasury destroyed about 51 million USDC on the Ethereum chain.
